@page "/navbar"
<PageTitle>Navbar - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="navbar">Navbar</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Navbar component renders a responsive navigation bar that adapts its
                CSS class names to the active design system.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Navbar&gt;
    &lt;A Href="/"&gt;Home&lt;/A&gt;
    &lt;A Href="/docs"&gt;Docs&lt;/A&gt;
    &lt;A Href="/pricing"&gt;Pricing&lt;/A&gt;
&lt;/Navbar&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>AriaLabel</td><td>string?</td><td>Accessibility label for the nav.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Navigation links and content.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="navbar-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Navbar</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Navbar</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Navbar component maps to the navbar class with navbar-expand
                and navbar-light or navbar-dark modifier classes. Bootstrap's navbar is fully
                responsive and collapses into a toggler button on small screens. The collapse
                behavior is handled by Bootstrap's JavaScript bundle. Navigation links inside
                the navbar receive the nav-link class automatically.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="navbar-daisyui">DaisyUI Navbar</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Navbar</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Navbar component maps to DaisyUI's navbar class. DaisyUI's navbar
                is a flex container that supports three content slots — navbar-start, navbar-center,
                and navbar-end — for positioning logo, links, and action buttons. It is CSS-only
                and theme-aware. Dropdown menus inside the navbar use DaisyUI's CSS-only dropdown
                component without JavaScript.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="navbar-basecoat">Basecoat Navbar</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Navbar</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Navbar component is composed from Tailwind flex utilities that
                create a horizontal navigation bar. The default Basecoat navbar uses flex layout
                with space-between alignment, consistent vertical padding, and a background color
                from the Tailwind theme. You can adjust the sticky behavior, shadow, and breakpoint
                collapse logic through additional Tailwind utilities in the Class parameter.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("navbar", "Navbar"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("navbar-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Navbar", 2),
    new TocItem("navbar-daisyui", "DaisyUI Navbar", 2),
    new TocItem("navbar-basecoat", "Basecoat Navbar", 2)
])" />

</div>
